## Dockerfile Standards

### Multi-Stage Builds (Always)

- Stage 1: Build (install deps, compile)
- Stage 2: Production (copy artifacts, run as non-root)
- Always use alpine or slim base images
- Always run as non-root user (USER appuser)

### Security

- Never store secrets in Dockerfiles or docker-compose
- Use .dockerignore to exclude .env, .git, node_modules
- Pin base image versions (node:22-alpine, NOT node:latest)

### Compose

- Use named volumes for persistent data
- Use healthchecks for all services
- Use depends_on with condition: service_healthy
- Expose only necessary ports
